ciences to analyze multicultural and postcolonial film, literature, and television, the contributors pioneer new techniques for appreciating all facets of the wonder of storytelling.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDiscourse analysis, Narrative. 0aFictionxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion pictures and literature. 0aNarration (Rhetoric) 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 0aPostcolonialism and the arts. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAldama, Arturo J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAldama, Frederick Luis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAldama, Frederick Luis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBreslin, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColm Hogan, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDannenberg, Hilary P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKim, Sue J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Sue-Im, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCracken, Ellen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNericcio, William Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNock-Hee Park, Josephine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPandit Hogan, Lalita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhelan, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrince, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomagnolo, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSh